race.comment: BON HOLLER (11) improving mare who ticks plenty of boxes today with the sharp weight drop. Just under a month between runs when jumped in trip for a plugging fourth over 1400m at Albury. Will roll forward and play a leading role. WRITE YOUR OWN (10) finally drawn a decent gate after being snagged back at his last two runs in town from awkward gates. Tommy Berry keeps the ride, and his best form is over this distance. Look for him charging late. TOMMY FLYER (6) big jump in grade and deserves his shot at this level. Shouldered the 61.5kg for a commanding on-pace win over this trip at the Sapphire Coast. Massive drop in weight with the claim and will take catching. ASSOCIATE (1) just under a month between runs second-up when a plugging eighth over this trip at Randwick. Will appreciate the weight drop and can return to form. BUENOS (18) lightly raced mare heading in the right direction. Key jockey change and at her top for this.
